  "title": "Senior Site Quantity Surveyor (Up to $6500 / 5 days / Kent Ridge)",
  "description": "<p>Job Title: Senior Site Quantity Surveyor (ID6009)<br />Location: Kent Ridge<br />Working Hour：Monday- Friday : 8:30am-5:30pm<br />Salary: $4,500 -$6,500<br /><br />Roles & Responsibilities<br />• Handle all contract administration matters with clients, consultants, and subcontractors, ensuring compliance with contractual obligations.<br />• Manage procurement activities: sourcing, calling quotations, cost comparisons, and issuing POs to achieve best value within budget.<br />• Prepare and submit client progress claims, evaluate subcontractors’ claims, and process payments to maintain healthy cash flow.<br />• Monitor project costs, update monthly cost reports, and advise PM/HQ on financial status and adjustments.<br />• Identify and submit variation order (VO) claims; review Architect Instructions and report cost/time implications.<br />• Conduct accurate quantity take-offs and measurements for claims and payments.<br />• Coordinate meetings with subcontractors and suppliers, assist in site coordination, and attend project/technical meetings to support smooth progress.<br />• Prepare and compile documents for monthly progress reports (cash flow, VO list, subcontractor list, AI list, etc.).<br />• Finalize project and trade costs, and assist PM in final account settlement with clients and subcontractors.<br />• Mentor and guide junior staff.<br /><br />Requirement<br />-Degree in Quantity survey<br />-Minimum of 8 years of relevant experience</p>",
